ðŸ”¹ CSS Interview Questions (Important & Basics)
ðŸ”¸ CSS Basics (Must-Know)
	1. What is CSS?
	CSS is used to style and design web pages.
	It controls how HTML elements look, such as colors, fonts, layout, spacing, and alignment.
	ðŸ‘‰ Simple words:
	CSS makes the website look good.
	One-line interview answer:
		CSS is used to style and design web pages.
	
	2. What does CSS stand for?
	CSS stands for Cascading Style Sheets.
	One-line interview answer:
		CSS stands for Cascading Style Sheets.
	
	3. Why do we use CSS?
	We use CSS to:
		â€¢ Make websites attractive
		â€¢ Control layout and design
		â€¢ Keep design separate from content
		â€¢ Apply the same style to multiple pages
		â€¢ Make websites responsive
	Simple interview answer:
		CSS is used to style web pages and separate design from HTML content.
	1. 
	2. 
	3. What are the different types of CSS?
	There are three types of CSS:
		1. Inline CSS
		2. Internal CSS
		3. External CSS
	One-line interview answer:
		CSS has three types: inline, internal, and external CSS.
	
	4. What is inline CSS?
	Inline CSS is written directly inside an HTML element using the style attribute.
	It affects only one element.
	Example:
	
	<p style="color:red;">Hello</p>
	One-line interview answer:
		Inline CSS is applied directly to an HTML element using the style attribute.
	
	5. What is internal CSS?
	Internal CSS is written inside the <style> tag within the <head> section of an HTML page.
	It styles one single page.
	Example:
	
	<style>
  p { color: blue; }
</style>
	One-line interview answer:
		Internal CSS is defined inside the style tag in the head section and applies to one page.
	
	6. What is external CSS?
	External CSS is written in a separate .css file and linked to HTML using the <link> tag.
	It can style multiple pages and is the best practice.
	Example:
	
	<link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
	3. 
	4. 
5. Which CSS type is best and why?
External CSS is the best.
Why?
	â€¢ It can style multiple pages
	â€¢ Makes code clean and reusable
	â€¢ Easy to maintain and update
	â€¢ Improves performance
One-line interview answer:
	External CSS is best because it is reusable, easy to maintain, and can style multiple pages.

6. What is CSS syntax?
CSS syntax defines how CSS rules are written.
It has three parts:
	1. Selector
	2. Property
	3. Value
Example:

p {
  color: red;
}
One-line interview answer:
	CSS syntax consists of a selector, property, and value.

7. What is a CSS selector?
A CSS selector is used to select HTML elements that we want to style.
Example:

p { color: blue; }
Here, p is the selector.
One-line interview answer:
	A CSS selector is used to target HTML elements for styling.

